This was an excellent class. The content is relevant to anyone wanting to start a business. It provides useful information and techniques for choosing and developing your business. Ambroise is an excellent and energetic teacher. I gave the class 4 stars instead of 5 only because of the peer grading approach used for some of the assignments. I sometimes got the impression that some students didn't fully understand the assignments, which of course can impact their grades. It turns out that an another student's misunderstanding can also affect your grade because he/she will be doing a peer review of your work. Language issues come into play since many of the students appear not to be native English speakers. The class could perhaps benefit from having a glossary that clearly defines some of the terms used during the course to clear up the confusion among some of the students.
This course is a good starting point for new entrepreneurs to learn about the entrepreneurial journey. Good tips and actionable advice is shared throughout the course
A very good presentation and lecture delivery.

If you are thinking about launching an app, product, or business, this course will force you to do some thinking about early-stage finance, sales, hiring, and operations.  The lectures are well produced, but the quality of content varies.  You'll get some tips for social engineering your way through cold calls and early sales meetings, but little about how to make the best of an online advertising budget.  Quizzes and assignments are reasonable, and as I said, force you to do at least some thinking about your priorities and the future of your business idea.

I've taken many classes on entrepreneurship and this one gives the best real life solutions to real problems an entrepreneur may encounter. While most classes offer theory based solutions, this one not only explains things in a practical way, but also gives step by step guides on how to do certain things. As other courses would say "find a partner to join you", this course gives you a complete guide on what to do and what not to do.The professor was extremely engaging and everything was interesting. There isn't a section of the course that wasn't useful. Everything is explained very clearly. Another very well thought out aspect of this course is that its interactive and feels very tailored to each viewer individually.The only thing that I didn't enjoy that much is the fact that there were always the same guest entrepreneurs and most of what they had to say couldn't really be applied. I wish more specific examples were chosen so that the theory could relate to very specific guests with the exact aspect of what is being taught.I would highly recommend this course to anyone wondering where to start their entrepreneurship journey. There's no better course to learn the basics without hours of theoretical concepts.
